{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4026f208-9a26-4a8c-833f-788c1b71f707","content":"Process **12345 isn't running** on this machine, so I can't inspect it directly. Here's how to determine the runtime and configure dumps:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Detect CoreCLR vs NativeAOT\n\nRun these against your **live process**:\n\n```bash\n# If this finds libcoreclr.so, it's CoreCLR. If not, it's likely NativeAOT.\ngrep -q 'libcoreclr\\.so' /proc/<PID>/maps && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"NativeAOT\"\n\n# Alternative: check for the JIT\nls -l /proc/<PID>/map_files/ | grep -i coreclr\n```\n\nNativeAOT apps are **fully self-contained** — no `libcoreclr.so`, no JIT.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Configure crash dumps\n\n#### For **CoreCLR** apps:\n\n```bash\n# Set environment variables (in your service/startup script):\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n\n# Create dump directory\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nOr use the **kernel core pattern** (works for both runtimes):\n\n```bash\n# System-wide kernel core dumps\necho '/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nulimit -c unlimited   # must be set in the process's shell/service\n```\n\n#### For **NativeAOT** apps:\n\nNativeAOT does **not** support the `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` variables. Use the **kernel core pattern** method above — it's the only option.\n\n```bash\necho '/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nulimit -c unlimited\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. For a systemd service (recommended)\n\n```ini\n# In your .service file:\n[Service]\nLimitCORE=infinity\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1       # CoreCLR only\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # CoreCLR only\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p\n```\n\nThen `sudo systemctl daemon-reload && sudo systemctl restart yourapp`.\n\n---\n\n**TL;DR:** Check `/proc/<PID>/maps` for `libcoreclr.so`. If present → CoreCLR (use `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump`). If absent → NativeAOT (use kernel `core_pattern` + `ulimit -c unlimited`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47cf3151-300c-4baf-92ae-51aead581ecc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist (PID 12345). Let me explain to the user how to determine the runtime and configure dumps, since I can't inspect a live process.\n\nLet me give them the diagnostic steps and configuration guidance.","outputTokens":788},"id":"3144cee5-7b91-4c40-b15d-b8e20fd9d897","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:07:41.880Z","parentId":"1dd24a25-5895-47e3-905b-bb3ba360eb84"}
